article.headline: Quinnipiac 78, Long Island U. 73
article.story: NEW YORK -- Justin Rutty had 23 points and 16 rebounds and Quinnipiac rallied for a 78-73 victory over Long Island University on Saturday. Jeremy Baker scored 13 points for the Bobcats (13-14, 9-7 Northeast Conference), while James Feldeine added 12 points and Brian Geffen 11. Jaytornah Wisseh scored 27 points, including going 11-for-11 on free throws, to lead the Blackbirds (14-13, 10-6), who had their 11-game home winning streak snapped. The Bobcats trailed 40-36 at halftime. Geffen's 3-pointer with 4:34 left put Quinnipiac on top for good, 64-61. The Blackbirds pulled within one twice after that but could not tie the score.
